GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 3
HOUSE BILL 146
Committee Substitute Favorable 4/16/25
Third Edition Engrossed 4/30/25
Short Title: Remote License Renewal/Active Duty Military. (Public)
Sponsors:
Referred to:
February 21, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT AUTHORIZING CONSECUTIVE REMOTE DRIVERS LICENSE RENEWALS
3 FOR ACTIVE DUTY MILITARY AND THEIR SPOUSES AND DEPENDENTS.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. G.S. 20-7 reads as rewritten:
6 "§ 20-7. Issuance and renewal of drivers licenses.
7 …
8 (f) Duration and Renewal of Licenses. – Drivers licenses shall be issued and renewed
9 pursuant to the provisions of this subsection:
10 …
11 (6) Remote renewal or conversion. – Subject to the following requirements and
12 limitations, the Division may offer remote renewal of a drivers license or
13 remote conversion of a full provisional license issued by the Division:
14 a. Requirements. – To be eligible for remote renewal or conversion under
15 this subdivision, a person must meet all of the following requirements:
16 …
17 4. For a remote renewal, the most recent renewal was an
18 in-person renewal and not a remote renewal under this
19 subdivision.subdivision, except that an active duty member of
20 the Armed Forces of the United States or a reserve component
21 of the Armed Forces of the United States, who is stationed
22 outside of this State, and the member's spouse and dependent
23 children may remotely renew a license a second consecutive
24 time if either of the following applies:
25 I. The license being renewed is not REAL ID compliant
26 pursuant to the REAL ID Act of 2005, 49 U.S.C. §
27 30301.
28 II. The license being renewed is REAL ID compliant but
29 is being converted to a non-REAL ID compliant license
30 for purposes of the renewal.
31 …."
32 SECTION 2. This act becomes effective October 1, 2025, and applies to licenses
33 renewed on or after that date.
